The paper discusses the use of continuous dynamical systems to model decision problems and online discussions using weighted bipolar argumentation frameworks. This falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) as it involves modeling and computation. The use of numerical algorithms and base classes for implementation suggests a focus on computational aspects, which could also place it under the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CY). Finally, the application of the approach to social interaction (online discussions) could also place it under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
